<p><em>Radiance: A Novel</em> is SF author <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carter%20Scholz" title="Wikipedia: Carter Scholz">Carter Scholz</a>â€™s second, literary, novel. It is a <em>roman Ã  clef</em> of the 1990s set at the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lawrence%20Livermore%20National%20Laboratory" title="Wikipedia: Lawrence Livermore National Laboratory">Lawrence Livermore National Laboratory</a>, centering on two nuclear physicists entangled in corruption, mid-life crises, institutional pressure, the end of the Cold War, nuclear bombs &amp; <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Strategic%20Defense%20Initiative" title="Wikipedia: Strategic Defense Initiative">Star Wars</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/existential%20risks" title="Wikipedia: existential risks">existential risks</a>, and the great scientific project of mankind. For relevant historical background, see the excerpts in the <a href="#appendices">appendices</a>.</p>
