<p>â€“He was one of these, shall I say, Marxist radical types. His mother cut him out of the family money. Hello, Philip. Weâ€™re waiting for Leo [pg10] as usual. So heâ€™s in Prague now selling laptops to the Czechs. Ah, the man himself.</p>
<p>â€“Whoâ€™s this youâ€™re talking about, sounds like heâ€™s figured out that free markets are diplomacy by other means. Everyone, this is Jef Thorpe, postdoc from the University of Utah, heâ€™s here to look us over. Jef worked with <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cold%20fusion%23Fleischmann.E2.80.93Pons%20experiment" title="Wikipedia: Cold fusion#Fleischmann.E2.80.93Pons experiment">Fish and Himmelhoch on cold fusion</a>, and I just want to say donâ€™t believe the conventional wisdom, something is happening there<a href="#fn13" class="footnoteRef" id="fnref13"><sup>13</sup></a>. Jef, this is Dennis Kihara, our new press officer, he takes the heat for my excesses. Bernd Dietz, materials and research. Frank Szabo, systems integration. Phil Quine, our x-ray focusing guru, Philip, Jefâ€™s done interesting work in your area, you should sit down with him. Okay, all present? Letâ€™s do it.</p>
