<h1><em>New Legends</em></h1>
<p><em>Radiance</em> was first published as the novella â€œRadianceâ€ (pg218-269; <a href="https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/182368464/1995-scholz-radiance.pdf">PDF scan</a>) in the June 1995 SF anthology <a href="http://www.amazon.com/New-Legends-Greg-Bear/dp/0312862016?tag=gwernnet-20"><em>New Legends</em></a> (edited by <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Greg%20Bear" title="Wikipedia: Greg Bear">Greg Bear</a>; ISBN 0312862016). Included in <em>New Legends</em> after â€œRadianceâ€ is the essay â€œOld Legendsâ€ (pg270-282; <a href="https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/182368464/1995-benford-oldlegends.pdf">PDF scan</a>) by <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gregory%20Benford" title="Wikipedia: Gregory Benford">Gregory Benford</a> about his experiences in SF and the military-research complex (see also Asimovâ€™s <a href="../docs/1963-asimov-sword-of-achilles">â€œThe Sword of Achillesâ€</a> &amp; <a href="../Culture%20is%20not%20about%20Esthetics#they-snatched-societys-brain">Culture is not about Esthetics</a>).</p>
<p>Bear categorized the <em>New Legends</em> stories into 6 sections:</p>
<ol type="1">
